---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Chile Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/chile/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Argentina for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/argentina' },
  { title: 'Uruguay for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uruguay' },
  { title: 'Ecuador for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/ecuador' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'chileFit', header: 'Chile Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$380-530/mo', chileFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$450-620/mo', chileFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$340-480/mo', chileFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'To 84', monthlyFrom: '$320-450/mo', chileFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Chilean ISAPRE', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'CLP 150,000-400,000', chileFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$340-530', annual: '$4,080-6,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$480-720', annual: '$5,760-8,640' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$640-950', annual: '$7,680-11,400' },
  { category: 'Chilean ISAPRE (Private)', monthly: 'CLP 150,000-400,000', annual: 'CLP 1.8M-4.8M' },
  { category: 'Chilean FONASA (Public)', monthly: '7% income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Chile 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Chile. ISAPRE private system, Santiago hospitals, retirement visa, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Chile"
  subheadline="Chile offers South America's best healthcare, economic stability, stunning geography, and welcoming retirement visa—from Atacama Desert to Patagonia."
  heroImage="/images/countries/chile-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Chile</h2>
  <p>
    Chile stands out in South America for stability, safety, and quality healthcare. The country offers incredible geographic diversity—from the world's driest desert to Patagonian glaciers. Santiago provides first-world amenities, while coastal and lake regions offer relaxed retirement options.
  </p>

  <p>
    Santiago offers excellent hospitals and cultural life. Valparaíso/Viña del Mar provide coastal living with good healthcare. The Lake District (Puerto Varas, Pucón) attracts nature lovers. The north offers dry climate; the south has cooler, European-like conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Best in South America; excellent private sector</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish (Chilean accent can be challenging)</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> CLP 1.2-2M/month (~$1,400-2,300)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Varies dramatically; Mediterranean in center</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Safest major South American country</li>
      <li><strong>Economy:</strong> Most stable and developed in region</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Chile's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Chile has a dual system: public FONASA and private ISAPREs (health insurance companies). The private system is excellent—world-class hospitals like Clínica Las Condes and Clínica Alemana rival facilities anywhere. About 80% of Chileans use FONASA; higher earners and expats typically use ISAPREs.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private hospitals in Santiago offer advanced care, English-speaking staff, and short wait times. Outside Santiago, quality varies but remains good in major cities. Medical costs are significantly lower than US but higher than other South American countries.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">ISAPRE Age Challenges</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Chilean ISAPREs can be difficult to join after 65 and premiums increase significantly with age. Some ISAPREs decline applicants over 65 or charge very high rates. International insurance may be more practical for older seniors. Plan carefully before age 65.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Chile offers welcoming options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Retirement Visa (Visa de Jubilado)</h3>
  <p>
    For those with pension income of at least $1,500/month (or less with savings). Valid 1 year, renewable. After 2 years can apply for permanent residence. Straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h3>Rentista Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with income from investments, rental properties, or other passive sources. Similar requirements to retirement visa. Good option for younger retirees not yet receiving pension.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After 2 years on temporary residence, you can apply for permanent residence. Provides full rights including access to FONASA (public health) if desired.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Chile:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance recommended (not strictly required)</li>
    <li><strong>ISAPRE option:</strong> Private Chilean insurance; can be difficult after 65</li>
    <li><strong>FONASA:</strong> Public option available to permanent residents</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Often best option for seniors; accepted for visa</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Chile</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      For seniors, international insurance is often the best option—Chilean ISAPREs have age restrictions and high premiums for elderly. International coverage provides excellent care at Clínica Las Condes and other top hospitals. Consider adding FONASA after permanent residence for local backup.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Chile, these providers offer strong coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Chile</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Direct billing at top Santiago hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), strong Latin America network</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive pricing for Americas</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Good US-based option for Americans; US coverage included</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage and pricing from providers that accept seniors for Chile.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Chile are moderate for the quality of care available:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>FONASA backup:</strong> After PR, join FONASA (7% income) as secondary coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> $5,000+ deductible reduces premiums significantly</li>
    <li><strong>Regional exclusions:</strong> Excluding US significantly reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>Direct pay:</strong> Chilean care is affordable; pay cash for minor issues</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month Social Security. Retiring to Santiago.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa and primary care. Direct billing at Clínica Las Condes.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$450/month. Excellent coverage at top Chilean hospitals plus US visits.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Retiring to Viña del Mar. £2,800/month combined pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Access to best Santiago hospitals. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$1,100/month combined. After PR, can add FONASA as backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian Snowbird, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 6 months Chile, 6 months Canada. Canadian pension + savings.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care worldwide. Covers both Canada and Chile. Single policy simplicity.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$400/month. No need for separate policies; comprehensive coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Chilean healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent—best in South America. Private hospitals like Clínica Las Condes, Clínica Alemana, and Clínica Santa María offer world-class care. Equipment is modern, doctors well-trained (many with US/European fellowships). English is common in private hospitals.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Chilean Spanish difficult to understand?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes, Chilean Spanish is notoriously fast and uses unique slang. Even fluent Spanish speakers from other countries may struggle initially. However, healthcare providers in private hospitals speak clearly and many speak English. You'll adapt over time.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about earthquakes?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Chile is seismically active—major earthquakes occur. However, Chilean building codes are among the world's strictest. Modern buildings are designed to withstand major quakes. The country handles earthquakes well due to experience and preparation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I get ISAPRE insurance over 65?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Difficult. Some ISAPREs won't accept new members over 60-65. Those that do charge very high premiums for seniors. If you want ISAPRE, join before 60 if possible. Otherwise, international insurance is usually better value and easier to obtain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Chile.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Chilean authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
